### 4. (Optional) Autostart

| OS | What to do |
|---|---|
| **Linux** (primary) | `mkdir -p ~/.config/systemd/user && cp autostart/systemd-user.service ~/.config/systemd/user/{{product}}-{{name}}.service && systemctl --user daemon-reload && systemctl --user enable --now {{product}}-{{name}}` |
| Windows | Edit `autostart/windows-task.xml` to point at your repo paths, then: `schtasks /Create /XML autostart\windows-task.xml /TN "{{product}}\{{name}}"` (elevated prompt, first time). |

### 5. IDE integration

> **There is no JetBrains plugin yet** for Claude Code or Agent SDK. The configs below give you a one-click "▶ Run" experience using built-in JetBrains/VSCode features.

**JetBrains** (PyCharm, IntelliJ, WebStorm):
1. Copy `ide/jetbrains-external-tool.xml` to `<repo-root>/.idea/tools/External Tools.xml` (merge if it exists)
2. Copy `ide/jetbrains-run-config.xml` to `<repo-root>/.idea/runConfigurations/Run_{{name}}_Locally.xml`
3. Restart the IDE — *Run {{name}} Locally* appears in both the Tools menu and the run-configuration dropdown

**VSCode / Cursor:**
- Merge the contents of `ide/vscode-tasks.json` into `<repo-root>/.vscode/tasks.json`
- Run via *Terminal → Run Task → Run {{name}} locally*

