## Deploy to a remote Linux host

From the skill folder:

```bash
scripts/deploy.sh <ip-or-host> <path-to-this-folder> --setup --enable-systemd
```

The script discovers an SSH key, tests connectivity, copies the zip, and (optionally) sets up the venv + systemd unit on the remote. It **does not** transport `.env` — you must populate secrets on the remote host manually. See `references/deploy.md` in the skill.

